						<summary>

						<p>On the <hi rend="italic">jagati,</hi> Bhikshāṭana shrine, Śivayōganāthasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 16: 987 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that Aiyāruḍaiyāṉ Poṟṟāḻi, a merchant of Kumaramāttāṇḍapuram in Tiraimūr-nāḍu on the southern bank of the river Kāvēri gifted a big lamp-stand as well as twenty four <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> for burning a perpetual lamp to the god Paramasvāmin of Tiruviśalūr in Amaṉinārāyaṇa-chaturvēdimaṅgalam, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāṉa-brahmadēya</hi> on the northern bank of the river Kāvēri. Both the <hi rend="italic">mahāsabhaiyār</hi> and <hi rend="italic">paṉmāhēśvarar</hi> agreed to protect the gift.</p>						

						</summary>
